# Project Guidelines

## Documentation Requirements

-   Update relevant documentation in /docs when modifying features
-   Keep README.md in sync with new capabilities
-   Maintain changelog entries in CHANGELOG.md

## Code Style & Patterns

-   Generate components using angular cli
-   Use TypeScript

## Testing Standards

-   Unit tests required for business logic

## Sensitive Files

DO NOT read or modify:

-   .env files
-   \*_/config/secrets._
-   \*_/_.pem
    \*/node_modules
-   Any file containing API keys, tokens, or credentials

## Security Practices

-   Never commit sensitive files
-   Use environment variables for secrets
-   Keep credentials out of logs and output

## Project Intelligence

-   Project initialized with Angular CLI.
-   Angular version 19 is being used.
-   The application name is newsfabric.
-   The project structure is based on Angular's component-based architecture.
-   The application will require a drag-and-drop interface.
